<dl id="n06155d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06155d">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06155d"> 155(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Which be they ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from Part Three. Christian Duty. The ten Commandments]</font> &ldquo;YOU SAID, THAT YOUR GODFATHERS AND GODMOTHERS DID PROMISE FOR YOU, THAT YOU SHOULD KEEP GOD&apos;S COMMANDMENTS. TELL ME HOW MANY THERE BE? <p>&ldquo;TEN.&rdquo;</p> <p>&ldquo;<mark>WHICH BE THEY?</mark>&rdquo;<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font></p> <p>The Ten Commandments are the foundation of all Christian Law and Duty. They are called the Decalogue, from the Greek deka, ten, logos, discourse.</p> <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 31</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
